# Distributed-queue trust policy (#289): exfiltration / confused-deputy gate.
#
# This file requires GitHub to have "Require review from Code Owners" enabled
# under branch protection for the target branch (Settings -> Branches -> main
# -> Require a pull request before merging -> Require review from Code
# Owners). CODEOWNERS itself is honored by GitHub independently of GitHub
# Actions -- it does not need any workflow to exist -- but it only *requires*
# review once that branch-protection option is turned on for this repo.
# Enabling it is a repo-admin action outside the scope of what this change
# modifies (branch protection is an access-control setting); see #289 for the
# open item.
/.github/security/distributed-trust-policy.json @wesleysimplicio
/.github/security/ @wesleysimplicio

# The authorizer, secure transport client, and credential/audit modules that
# enforce the trust policy above are equally security-critical -- a change to
# any of them can silently widen what the policy allows, so they get the same
# owner-review requirement as the policy data file itself.
/scripts/distributed_trust_policy.py @wesleysimplicio
/simplicio_loop/secure_transport.py @wesleysimplicio
/scripts/security_audit_log.py @wesleysimplicio
/scripts/short_lived_credentials.py @wesleysimplicio
/docs/adr/0003-distributed-proof-trust-boundaries.md @wesleysimplicio
/docs/security/distributed-credentials-runbook.md @wesleysimplicio
